NAME: Mission name
NAME TYPE: SKOS RDF concept label - exactly one preferred label per mission, the most common/recent name, often the acronymn, but not always, multiple alt/hidden labels allowed but not required
MISSION TYPE: Existing mission types, exactly one per mission, frontend facet, see validate tab
MISSION TYPE PLUS: Phase II: new mission types, once field populated with data will be combined with existing mission types, see validate tab
MISSION CATEGORY: Phase II: discipline/subject based, currently set up as one per mission, but if multiple are needed per mission this structure can be revised, see validate tab
LAUNCH VEHICLE: This column might get phased out eventually, existing only through links between missions, but populate for now where applicable
CELESTIAL BODIES: Phase II: Pipe delimited list (add flyby, orbit, landing afterwards in parenthesis if known) - for now just listed in a cell but data structure likely to change - use the Unified Astronomical Thesaurus (UAT) concept names: https://astrothesaurus.org/thesaurus/search-the-uat/
ORBIT: Phase II: Only a few Earth orbits listed currently, but more to be added soon
PROGRAM COST: Don't waste time trying to track down this number, but if you happen to come across it, then add it in

NAME: Extracted from mission source(s), listed one per line in export, so a lot of the data below is repetitive, but it's a bit easier this way
NAME TYPE: Derived from mission source(s), assigned locally
MISSION TYPE: Derived from mission source(s), assigned locally
MISSION TYPE PLUS: Derived from mission source(s), assigned locally
MISSION CATEGORY: Derived from mission source(s), assigned locally
SPACE: Derived from mission source(s), assigned locally
TIME: Derived from mission source(s), assigned locally
